@page "/getting-started"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web

<PageTitle>Getting Started with Markdn</PageTitle>

<CascadingValue Value="@_pageMetadata">

<h1 id="getting-started-with-markdn">Getting Started with Markdn</h1>
<p>Welcome to Markdn! This guide will help you understand the basics of using Markdn for your Blazor applications.</p>
<h2 id="what-is-markdn">What is Markdn?</h2>
<p>Markdn is a modern, type-safe content management system that lets you write content in Markdown and automatically generates Blazor components from it.</p>
<h2 id="key-features">Key Features</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Type-Safe Content Collections</strong>: Define schemas for your content and get compile-time type safety</li>
<li><strong>Markdown to Blazor</strong>: Automatically convert Markdown files to Blazor Razor components</li>
<li><strong>Frontmatter Support</strong>: Use YAML frontmatter to add metadata to your content</li>
<li><strong>Source Generation</strong>: Leverage C# source generators for optimal performance</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h2>
<ol>
<li>Create a collections.json file</li>
<li>Add markdown files with frontmatter</li>
<li>Use the generated content service</li>
</ol>
<p>That's it! You're now ready to use Markdn in your project.</p>


</CascadingValue>

